The Brandon University Bobcats were unable to complete their Canada West conference women’s volleyball sweep of the host Calgary Dinos on Saturday. 
Jodie Baker had seven kills, two blocks and an ace, but it wasn’t enough as the Bobcats dropped to 1-3 on the season with a 3-0 (25-20, 25-22, 25-12) loss to the Dinos (3-1), who are ranked eighth in the country. Shanlee McLennan and Gillian Leech both added six kills with Leech serving up a pair of aces. Please subscribe to view full article.
